                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 D 74/238: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-04T12:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1920—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 5:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. Mrs. Doty formerly prisoner in Petrograd reported at consulate August 2nd and
                    left town immediately. She left Russia about July 1st in company with other
                    Americans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
